name: Eggs
description: They are laid by female animals of many different species, including birds, reptiles, amphibians, a few mammals, and fish, and many of these have been eaten by humans for thousands of years.

name: Flour
description: It is a powder made by grinding raw grains, roots, beans, nuts, or seeds.

name: Milk
description: It is a nutrient-rich liquid food produced by the mammary glands of mammals.

name: Olive oil
description: is a liquid fat obtained from olives, a traditional tree crop of the Mediterranean Basin, produced by pressing whole olives and extracting the oil.

name: Spice
description: It is a seed, fruit, root, bark, or other plant substance primarily used for flavoring or coloring food.

name: Sugar
description: It is the generic name for sweet-tasting, soluble carbohydrates, many of which are used in food.
